":"Author/Wanping Chen","target":"Author/Wanping Chen","line":119},{"title":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","line":120},{"title":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","target":"Author/Wan-Ping Chen","line":121},{"title":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","target":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","line":122},{"title":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","target":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","line":123},{"title":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","target":"Author/Chin-Chu Chen","line":124},{"title":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","target":"Author/Chen Chin-Chu","line":125},{"title":"Author/Chiao-Fang Teng","target":"Author/Chiao-Fang Teng","line":126},{"title":"Author/Chih-Chuan Teng","target":"Author/Chih-Chuan Teng","line":127},{"title":"Author/Chih-Chuan Teng","target":"Author/Chih-Chuan Teng","line":128},{"title":"Author/Chih-Chuan Teng","target":"Author/Chih-Chuan Teng","line":129},{"title":"Author/Chien-Heng Shen","target":"Author/Chien-Heng Shen","line":130},{"title":"Author/Chien-Heng Shen","target":"Author/Chien-Heng Shen","line":131},{"title":"Author/Meng-Che Hsieh","target":"Author/Meng-Che Hsieh","line":132},{"title":"Author/Meng-Chiao Hsieh","target":"Author/Meng-Chiao Hsieh","line":133},{"title":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","target":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","line":134},{"title":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","target":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","line":135},{"title":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","target":"Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo","line":136},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/lee_induction_2019/lee_induction_2019.pdf","line":138}],"metadata":{"id":"lee_induction_2019","type":"article-journal","title":"Induction Apoptosis of Erinacine A in Human Colorectal Cancer Cells Involving the Expression of TNFR, Fas, and Fas Ligand via the JNK/p300/p50 Signaling Pathway With Histone Acetylation.","issued":{"date-parts":[[2019]]},"DOI":"10.3389/fphar.2019.01174","container-title":"Frontiers in Pharmacology","abstract":"Erinacine A, which is the major one of the bioactive diterpenoid compounds extracted from cultured mycelia of H. erinaceus, displays great anti-tumorigenic activity. However, the molecular mechanisms underlying erinacine A inducing cancer cell apoptosis in CRC remain unclear. This study shows that treatment with erinacine A not only triggers the activation of extrinsic apoptosis pathways (TNFR, Fas, Fas-L and caspases), but also suppresses the expression of anti-apoptotic molecules Bcl-2 and Bcl-XL via a time-dependent manner in DLD-1 cells. Furthermore, phosphorylation of Jun N-terminus kinase (JNK1/2), NFκB p50, p300 is involved in erinacine A-induced cancer cell apoptosis. Inhibition of these three signaling pathways by SP600125 (an inhibitor for JNK1/2), C646 (an inhibitor for p300), or PDTI (an inhibitor for NFκB) blocks erinacine A–induced transcriptional activation implicates histone H3K9K14ac (Acetyl Lys9/Lys14) of the TNFR, Fas, and Fas-L as promoters. Moreover, histochemical and immunohistochemical analyses revealed that erinacine A treatment significantly induced the TNFR, Fas, and Fas-L levels in the in vivo xenograft mouse model. Together, these results demonstrated an increase in the cellular transcriptional levels of TNFR, Fas, and Fas-L by erinacine A induction to cell apoptosis via the activation of the JNK, p300, and NFκB p50 signaling modules thereby providing a new mechanism for erinacine A treatment in vitro and in vivo.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Lee","given":"Ko-Chao","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Ko-Chao","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Kam-Fai","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Kam-Fai","literal":""},{"family":"Tung","given":"Shui-Yi","literal":""},{"family":"Tung","given":"Shui-Yi","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Wen-Shih","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Wen-Shih","literal":""},{"family":"Huang","given":"Wen-Shih","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li-Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Lee","given":"Li-Ya","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wanping","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan-Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Wan-Ping","literal":""},{"family":"Chin-Chu","given":"Chen","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chin-Chu","literal":""},{"family":"Chen","given":"Chin-Chu","literal":""},{"family":"Chin-Chu","given":"Chen","literal":""},{"family":"Teng","given":"Chiao-Fang","literal":""},{"family":"Teng","given":"Chih-Chuan","literal":""},{"family":"Teng","given":"Chih-Chuan","literal":""},{"family":"Teng","given":"Chih-Chuan","literal":""},{"family":"Shen","given":"Chien-Heng","literal":""},{"family":"Shen","given":"Chien-Heng","literal":""},{"family":"Hsieh","given":"Meng-Che","literal":""},{"family":"Hsieh","given":"Meng-Chiao","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsing-Chun","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsing-Chun","literal":""},{"family":"Kuo","given":"Hsing-Chun","literal":""}],"citation-key":"lee_induction_2019","year":"2019","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Induction Apoptosis of Erinacine A in Human Colorectal Cancer Cells Involving the Expression of TNFR, Fas, and Fas Ligand via the JNK/p300/p50 Signaling Pathway With Histone Acetylation."],"author-links":["[[Author/Ko-Chao Lee]]","[[Author/Ko-Chao Lee]]","[[Author/Kam-Fai Lee]]","[[Author/Kam-Fai Lee]]","[[Author/Shui-Yi Tung]]","[[Author/Shui-Yi Tung]]","[[Author/Wen-Shih Huang]]","[[Author/Wen-Shih Huang]]","[[Author/Wen-Shih Huang]]","[[Author/Li-Ya Lee]]","[[Author/Li-Ya Lee]]","[[Author/Wanping Chen]]","[[Author/Wan-Ping Chen]]","[[Author/Wan-Ping Chen]]","[[Author/Chen Chin-Chu]]","[[Author/Chin-Chu Chen]]","[[Author/Chin-Chu Chen]]","[[Author/Chen Chin-Chu]]","[[Author/Chiao-Fang Teng]]","[[Author/Chih-Chuan Teng]]","[[Author/Chih-Chuan Teng]]","[[Author/Chih-Chuan Teng]]","[[Author/Chien-Heng Shen]]","[[Author/Chien-Heng Shen]]","[[Author/Meng-Che Hsieh]]","[[Author/Meng-Chiao Hsieh]]","[[Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo]]","[[Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo]]","[[Author/Hsing-Chun Kuo]]"],"attachment":["[[biblib/lee_induction_2019/lee_induction_2019.pd